      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Loath to rule any of these out on their best. LITTLEBOURKESTREET (8) is a former South Australian who is having her first run for the new yard and does boast a good fresh-up record. Has the inside and will stalk a hot pace. AUXILIARY (1) is a former Victorian kicking off in the NT and also has good early dash. Best figures stack right up. DAD BOD (4) is going well with a two-length win two back then placing here last time. Another with pace and will has a fitness edge. BRAZEN BON (3) ran fourth in the same race as DAD BOD last time and will be winding up strongly. Has a good record at this course and distance. LA BOQUERIA (9) was solid fresh and drawn much better this time.",
